'''Edward J. Hall''' ('''Ned Hall''') is an American philosopher and Norman E. Vuilleumier Professor and Chair of the Department of [[Philosophy]] at [[Harvard University]]. He is known for his expertise on [[philosophy of science]] and [[epistemology]].<ref>[http://www.thecrimson.com/article/2015/3/12/ned-hall/ Professor Profile: Ned Hall]</ref><ref>[http://artsandhumanities.fas.harvard.edu/people/ned-hall Ned Hall]</ref><ref>[http://www.lapaul.org/papers/causation-maudlin-review.pdf L. A. Paul and Ned Hall. Causation: A User’s Guide] Review by [[Tim Maudlin]]</ref>
