'''Erica Benner''' is a [[Political philosophy|political philosopher]] who has held academic posts at [[St Antony's College, Oxford]], the [[London School of Economics]] and [[Yale University]]. She was awarded a DPhil by Oxford in 1993. She is the author of the books ''Really Existing Nationalisms'' (Oxford University Press, 1995), ''Machiavelli's Ethics'' (Princeton University Press, 2009), ''Machiavelli's Prince: A New Reading'' (Oxford University Press, 2013) and ''Be Like the Fox: Machiavelli's Lifelong Quest for Freedom'' (Penguin Allen Lane, 2017).<ref name=CV>{{cite web|url=http://www.ericabenner.com/academic.html|title=Academic|publisher=Erica Benner|accessdate=20 July 2018}}</ref> ''Be Like the Fox'' was described by [[Terry Eagleton]] as "lively, compulsively readable biography",<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2017/mar/15/be-like-a-fox-by-erica-benner-machiavelli|title=Be Like a Fox by Erica Benner review – was Machiavelli really not Machiavellian?|work=The Guardian|date=15 March 2018}}</ref> chosen by [[Julian Baggini]] as one of his picks for ''The Guardian's'' best books of 2017 list,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2017/nov/26/best-books-of-2017-part-two|title=Best books of 2017 – part two|work=The Guardian|date=26 November 2017|accessdate=21 July 2018}}</ref> and shortlisted for the 2018 [[Elizabeth Longford Prize|Elizabeth Longford Prize for Historical Biography]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://elhb.uk/2018-shortlist/|title=2018 Shortlist|publisher=Elizabeth Longford Prize for Historical Biography|date=5 April 2018|accessdate=20 July 2018}}</ref>

