{{short description|painting by René Magritte}} {{Infobox artwork |title = The Treachery of Images |image = MagrittePipe.jpg |artist = [[René Magritte]] |year = 1929 |medium = [[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] |height_metric = 60.33 |width_metric = 81.12 |metric_unit = cm |imperial_unit = in |museum = [[Los Angeles County Museum of Art]]<ref name="lacma1">''[http://collections.lacma.org/node/239578 La Trahison des images (Ceci n'est pas une pipe)]'', Los Angeles County Museum of Art</ref> }}__NOTOC__
'''''The Treachery of Images''''' ({{lang-fr|La Trahison des images}}) is a painting by [[surrealist]] painter [[René Magritte]]. It is also known as ''This is Not a Pipe''<ref>{{cite book|last=Foucault|first=Michel|title=This is Not a Pipe|others=James Harkness (Editor, Translator), René Magritte (Illustrator)|location=Berkeley|publisher=University of California Press|date=2008|edition=2nd|isbn=9780520236943|url=https://monoskop.org/images/9/99/Foucault_Michel_This_Is_Not_a_Pipe.pdf}}</ref> and ''The Wind and the Song''.<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1080/00043249.1985.10792322|jstor=776809|title=Words and Images: A Persistent Paradox|journal=Art Journal|volume=45|issue=4|pages=335|year=2014|last1=Bowman|first1=Russell}}</ref> Magritte painted it when he was 30 years old. It is currently on display at the [[Los Angeles County Museum of Art]].<ref name="lacma1"/>
The painting shows a [[smoking pipe (tobacco)|pipe]]. Below it, Magritte painted, {{lang|fr|"Ceci n'est pas une pipe."}}; French for "This is not a pipe." {{Quote|text = The famous pipe. How people reproached me for it! And yet, could you stuff my pipe? No, it's just a representation, is it not? So if I had written on my picture 'This is a pipe', I'd have been lying! |author = René Magritte<ref name="Torczyner1">{{cite book|last=Torczyner|first=Harry|title=Magritte: Ideas and Images|page=71|isbn=9780810913004}}</ref>}}
The theme of pipes with the text "Ceci n'est pas une pipe" is extended in ''Les Mots et Les Images'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ideophone.org/magritte-on-words-and-images/ |title=René Magritte - Les mots et les images|website=The Ideophone|accessdate=25 July 2017}}</ref> ''La Clé des Songes'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artnet.com/artists/ren%C3%A9-magritte/la-cl%C3%A9-des-songes-a-2t31F4pOvilbRkGeHVsjOw2 |title=René Magritte - La Clé des Songes.|website=Artnet|accessdate=25 July 2017}}</ref> ''Ceci n'est pas une pipe (L'air et la chanson)'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artnet.com/artists/ren%C3%A9-magritte/ceci-nest-pas-une-pipe-lair-et-le-chanson-iLdZ-PjAr0bdok6iheXnLA2 |title=René Magritte - Ceci n'est pas une pipe (L'air et le chanson)|website=Artnet|accessdate=25 July 2017}}</ref> ''The Tune and Also the Words'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artic.edu/aic/collections/artwork/119129 |title=René Magritte - L'air et le chanson|website=Art Institute Chicago|accessdate=25 July 2017}}</ref> ''Ceci n’est pas une pomme'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://muides2.free.fr/HIDA/Magritte/trahisondesimages.pdf |title=René Magritte - Ceci n’est pas une pomme|accessdate=25 July 2017}}</ref> and ''Les Deux Mystères''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abcgallery.com/M/magritte/magritte54.html |title=René Magritte - The Two Mysteries.|website=abcgallery.com |accessdate=3 October 2010}}</ref>
The painting is sometimes given as an example of [[meta message]] conveyed by [[paralanguage]].<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1075/sl.28.1.14hai|title=Review of "Languages within language: An evolutive approach" by Ivan Fonagy|journal=Studies in Language|volume=28|pages=246|year=2004|last1=Haiman|first1=John}}</ref> Compare with [[Alfred Korzybski|Korzybski]]'s ""The word is not the thing" and "[[Map–territory relation|The map is not the territory]]" as well as [[Diderot]]'s ''[[This is not a story]]''.{{-}}
